      <sec>
        <title>2.1.4 Finding the boundary points</title>
        <p>After determining the optimal number of segments into which to divide the data from <xref rid="E1" ref-type="disp-formula">Equaion (1)</xref>, we next find their boundary points. Using Bayesâ theorem, the posterior for <italic toggle="yes">n</italic> is</p>
        <disp-formula id="E18">
          <label>(18)</label>
          <mml:math id="M18" display="block" overflow="scroll">
            <mml:mrow>
