        <p>Although with <xref rid="E22" ref-type="disp-formula">Equation (22)</xref> it is possible to approximate analytically the integral over <italic toggle="yes">Ï</italic> in <xref rid="E20" ref-type="disp-formula">Equation (20)</xref> by extending the range of the integrand to <inline-formula id="IE72"><mml:math id="IM72" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mn>0</mml:mn><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mo>â</mml:mo><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math></inline-formula>, the resulting expression prevents us from summing over <bold><italic toggle="yes">n</italic></bold> using variable elimination. Instead, we swap the sum and the integral to write</p>
