        <p>and numerically evaluate, using variable elimination to sum over <bold><italic toggle="yes">n</italic></bold> in <xref rid="E23" ref-type="disp-formula">Equation (23)</xref> for each <italic toggle="yes">Ï</italic> chosen by the integration algorithm.</p>
        <p>We find the expected boundary points via <xref rid="E19" ref-type="disp-formula">Equation (19)</xref>, again numerically integrating over <italic toggle="yes">Ï</italic>.</p>
        <p><bold>Performing the integration:</bold> To stabilize the numerical integration, we scale the integrand of <xref rid="E23" ref-type="disp-formula">Equation (23)</xref> by its value at the most likely value of <italic toggle="yes">Ï</italic>, making the integrand nearly always less than one and preventing overflow. We use expectation-maximization (EM) to estimate the most likely <italic toggle="yes">Ï</italic> for a given <italic toggle="yes">M</italic>. The EM algorithm finds the <italic toggle="yes">Ï</italic> that maximizes <inline-formula id="IE73"><mml:math id="IM73" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>P</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>D</mml:mi><mml:mo>|</mml:mo><mml:mi>M</mml:mi><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mo>Ï</mml:mo><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math></inline-formula> (<xref rid="btad688-B2" ref-type="bibr">Bishop 2006</xref>). We guess a value of <italic toggle="yes">Ï</italic>, <italic toggle="yes">Ï<sub>o</sub></italic> say, and find <inline-formula id="IE74"><mml:math id="IM74" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>P</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi mathvariant="bold-italic">n</mml:mi><mml:mo>|</mml:mo><mml:mi>D</mml:mi><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mo>Ï</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mi>o</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mrow><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mi>M</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math></inline-formula> from <xref rid="E18" ref-type="disp-formula">Equation (18)</xref>. To update <italic toggle="yes">Ï<sub>o</sub></italic>, we maximize <inline-formula id="IE75"><mml:math id="IM75" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>Q</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mo>Ï</mml:mo><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mo>Ï</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mi>o</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math></inline-formula> with respect to <italic toggle="yes">Ï</italic>, where</p>
        <disp-formula id="E24">
